  "prompt": "Is there a Church that doesn't believe in Trinity?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several Christian denominations and churches that do not believe in the traditional doctrine of the Trinity. Some of these include:\n\n1. **Unitarian Universalists**: They reject the concept of the Trinity and have a more inclusive approach to spirituality and religious belief.\n\n2. **Jehovah's Witnesses**: They reject the Trinity, believing instead that Jesus is not God but God's first creation and a separate entity from God the Father.\n\n3. **Christadelphians**: They believe that Jesus is the Son of God but do not accept the Trinity, viewing God as a singular entity.\n\n4. **Oneness Pentecostals**: They reject the traditional Trinity doctrine in favor of the belief that God manifests himself in various forms, such as Father, Son, and Holy Spirit, but not as three distinct persons.\n\nThese groups interpret the relationship between God the Father, Jesus Christ, and the Holy Spirit differently than mainstream Trinitarian Christianity.",
